==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fowlers solution
<hw>Fow"ler's so*lu"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>An aqueous solution of
arsenite of potassium, of such strength that one hundred parts represent
one part of arsenious acid, or white arsenic; -- named from
<etsep>Fowler</etsep>, an English physician who first brought it into
use.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fox</ent>⟦br⟧
